content: Created `pyproject.toml` with setuptools build configuration, a `run-benchmark` console-script entry point, and minimal pytest settings (including `pythonpath=src`) to run the benchmark CLI consistently.

output.code:
from pathlib import Path
import json, textwrap, os, re, sys
target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('pyproject.toml')
target_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

chunks = [
"""[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=68", "wheel"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta\"""",
"""[project]
name = "generated_script_1766440494796"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Benchmark contract + CLI runner"
readme = "README.md"
requires-python = ">=3.10"
license = {text = "MIT"}
dependencies = []

[project.optional-dependencies]
dev = ["pytest>=7.0"]

[project.scripts]
run-benchmark = "run_benchmark:main\"""",
"""[tool.setuptools]
package-dir = {"" = "src"}

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]""",
"""[tool.pytest.ini_options]
testpaths = ["tests"]
addopts = "-q"
pythonpath = ["src"]"""
]
final_text = '\n'.join(block.strip('\n') for block in chunks).strip() + '\n'
target_path.write_text(final_text, encoding='utf-8')
print('FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml')
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
